                                <button class="accordion"><h2>BRIEF OUTLINE OF THE ORGANIZATION<i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i> </h2></button>
                                    <div class="panel">
                                        <p>SUKHI 222, is a USA-based international NGO serving the poor and needy people especially to assure a scalable, sustainable, dignified, affordable access to a minimum of 2 gallons of fresh water, 2,000 nutritional calories, and 200 cubic feet of secure tenure.</p>
                                        <p>SUKHI 222 has been established by a group of senior human rights activists and social development workers.</p>
                                        <p>It is a registered not-for-profit organization operating under the fiscal sponsorship of IFERS, Institute for Education Research and Scholarships. </p>
                                        <p>It works at international level, through its regional and country offices and in collaboration with its local collaborators.</p>
                                        <p>Reaching out to the poorest of the poor in target areas without respect to caste, colour and creed. SUKHI 222 works through partnerships to bring about lasting change in the lives of vulnerable people. SUKHI 222 is an independent entity within our country with a distinctly national identity. An active Board of Executive Committee governs SUKHI 222.</p>
                                        <p>For the purpose of this project, the poorest of the poor are defined as individuals among the society who cannot meet  or get access to the minimum wage of GHS10.65p per day its equivalence of 2.05 United States Dollar.</p>
                                        <h4>VISION STATEMENT</h4>
                                        <p>To envision a world where all of humankind understands their role in civilized society and has the freedom to achieve their goals. </p>
                                        <h4>MISSION STATEMENT</h4>
                                        <p>“Promoting and enabling dignified access within civil society to sustainable access of adequate food water and shelter to all.” </p>
                                    </div>

                                <button class="accordion"><h2>BRIEF OUTLINE AND RATIONALE OF THE PROJECT<i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i> </h2></button>
                                    <div class="panel">
                                        <p>SUKHI 222 is an Organization that is committed to serve the vulnerable people in the community for their Sustainable Development and also attain the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) by providing clean and safe drinking water to the targeted communities. SUKHI 222 has been extending services like the provision of water filters in the target areas. There is no doubt that Water and Sustainable Development are inextricably linked. Without adequate supplies and management of fresh water sources, sustainable development simply cannot take place. </p>
                                        <p>However, the resources are limited but there is a great need for safe water in the backward rural areas in the community. There are many communities where the dugouts provided by the Government are damaged and need rehabilitation and deepening to draw water. In these areas the rural households have no access to water during the dry season.Most use water from tube wells or open wells, while a small minority uses tanks and springs. Hence, there is a high dependence on groundwater for drinking and other domestic purposes. </p>
                                        <p>Poor rural households collect water from community sources, which are often remote and spend much time in collecting water. The collected water is a major causeof waterborne diseases. </p>
                                        <p>Diseases due to contamination of drinking water constitute a major burden on health as most of these vulnerable populace do not have adequate access to health facilities and even insurance.Improvement in the quality of drinking water will significantly benefit the health and wellbeing of people. </p>
                                        <p>Therefore, the organization is working towards providing safe drinking water to the maximum extent possible in its target villages. </p>
                                        <p>Children are perhaps the most cheerful and omnipresent facet of rural villages. Curious, unafraid to stare, and ready to smile, they are unconcerned about their running noses, bare feet, unkept hair and ragged clothes. If they are fortunate enough to have a school anda regular and dedicated teacher and if their parents can spare them from work, they get an education. </p>
                                        <p>But more often than not, the conditions are not ripe. They are often uninformed about health issues, hygiene and sanitation, since their mothers are often uninformed too. </p>
