                                        <p>The project has a long term benefit that the Rehabilitationof the dugoutis managed by the community itself. The Project will be aligned with good sanitation and hygiene principles. The community people will be educated on proper hygiene and sanitation practices and management. The children will attend their respective schools instead of walking miles in search of water. The community came forward for their participation in owning a rain harvest system and also rehabilitating the dugout. The training will be given to stakeholders of the community in capacity building and awareness on Water and Sanitation to handle the water infrastructure in a more proper way. </p>
                                        <p>Operation and Maintenance is required to ensure the sustainability of any project in which a new infrastructure has been put into place. </p>
